4. **gs-5-4** One-Minute Changes (7 min) -- 4 barre chord pairs timed drill, including the critical C#m-to-B cross-shape transition
5. **gs-5-5** Sliding Barres (6 min) -- chromatic escalator up and down the neck in both shapes
6. **gs-5-6** Sol Del Sur Song Study (10 min) -- THE anchor: C#m-B-F#, harmonic analysis of borrowed IV, syncopated strum, speed ladder 70-100 BPM
7. **gs-5-7** Island Fever Song Study (8 min) -- Fm-Bb-Ab-Eb with capo and full-barre options, dreamy feel contrast
8. **gs-5-8** Just Yesterday Song Study (8 min) -- E-G-A-Em at 130 BPM, mixing open and barre voicings at speed
9. **gs-5-9** Sunset Garage Song Study (8 min) -- G-B-C-D at 142 BPM, single barre among open chords
10. **gs-5-10** Barre Chord Improv (8 min) -- create your own 3-chord barre loop, choose strum style
11. **gs-5-11** Extended Jam (10 min) -- 5+ minute Sol Del Sur performance with dynamic contrast, recorded

**Key pedagogy baked in:** Start at fret 5 (not fret 1), bony side technique, thumb-behind-barre, one-minute changes drill, rep-with-reset, sleep consolidation reminders, speed ladders. All four specified songs are covered. `chordVoicings` and `fretboard` fields used where appropriate. All backing track paths reference existing files. Sarah notes reference Sun Room's Jazzmaster/Tubescreamer/Deluxe Reverb setup, the i-bVII-IV harmonic pattern, and the "simple is better" philosophy.</result>
